/alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/navigate/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="NAVIGATE Summer School"/><published>2025-07-24T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-07-24T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/navigate</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/navigate/"><![CDATA[<p>Participation in the Summer School NAVIGATE at TU Delft.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/delft_ss-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/delft_ss-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/delft_ss-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/delft_ss.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="conference"/><category term="IROS"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Connected autonomous vehicles and Intelligent Transportation Systems.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Presentation at ECC 2025</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/ecc2025/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Presentation at ECC 2025"/><published>2025-07-24T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-07-24T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/ecc2025</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2025/ecc2025/"><![CDATA[<p>Presentation European Control Conference 2025, in Thessaloniki, Greece.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/ecc2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/ecc2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/ecc2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/ecc2025.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="conference"/><category term="IROS"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Presentation at IEEE ECC 2025.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Workshop at MIT</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/mit-ws/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Workshop at MIT"/><published>2024-07-16T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-07-16T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/mit-ws</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/mit-ws/"><![CDATA[<p>Workshop on optimal control problems and model predictive control for autonomous systems hosted by MIT CSAIL.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/mit_workshop-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/mit_workshop-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/mit_workshop-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/mit_workshop.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="workshop"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Workshop on optimal control problems and model predictive control for autonomous systems.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Presentation at ICRA 2024</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/icra2024/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Presentation at ICRA 2024"/><published>2024-05-15T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-05-15T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/icra2024</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/icra2024/"><![CDATA[<p>Presentation on model predictive control and control barrier functions for autonomous surface vessels at the IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA) 2024, in Yokohama, Japan.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/icra2024-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/icra2024-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/icra2024-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/icra2024.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="conference"/><category term="ICRA"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Presentation on model predictive control and control barrier functions for autonomous surface vessels at IEEE ICRA 2024.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Talk at TU Delft</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/delft-talk/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Talk at TU Delft"/><published>2024-04-16T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-04-16T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/delft-talk</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2024/delft-talk/"><![CDATA[<p>Talk at Delft University of Technology about some of my previous and current research work, and what we do in the MECO Research Team at KU Leuven. I focused on the subjects of robust control and fast optimal motion planning, and their application to single and multi-agent autonomous systems in water, air and ground.</p> <p>Thanks to Elia Trevisan and Prof. Javier Alonso-Mora for the invitation and tour around the lab, and for facilitating discussions with plenty of researchers working on similar topics.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/talk_tudelft-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/talk_tudelft-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/talk_tudelft-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/talk_tudelft.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="workshop"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Talk on past research and work at MECO.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Presentation at ICRA 2023</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2023/icra2023/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Presentation at ICRA 2023"/><published>2023-06-01T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-06-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2023/icra2023</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2023/icra2023/"><![CDATA[<p>Presentation on deep reinforcement learning for autonomous surface vessels at the IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA) 2023 in London, England.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/icra2023-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/icra2023-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/icra2023-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/icra2023.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="conference"/><category term="ICRA"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Presentation on deep reinforcement learning for autonomous surface vessels at IEEE ICRA 2023.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Control Robusto para Barcos Autónomos — CIDiTec</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/ciditec-control/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Control Robusto para Barcos Autónomos — CIDiTec"/><published>2022-08-16T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-08-16T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/ciditec-control</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/ciditec-control/"><![CDATA[<p>Alejandro González es estudiante de la Maestría en Ciencias de la Ingeniería, y está desarrollando algoritmos que puedan contrarrestar factores externos en barcos. El laboratorio de Robótica forma parte del CIDiTec de la Escuela de Ingeniería y Ciencias.</p> <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9 mt-3"> <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0Nx9AH2MgEU" allowfullscreen=""></iframe> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="media"/><category term="research"/><category term="ASV"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[CIDiTec video feature on developing algorithms to counteract external factors in autonomous boats.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Barcos Autónomos Diseñados Contra Viento y Marea</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/barcos-autonomos/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Barcos Autónomos Diseñados Contra Viento y Marea"/><published>2022-01-14T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-01-14T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/barcos-autonomos</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2022/barcos-autonomos/"><![CDATA[<p>Investigadores del Tec diseñan controladores más robustos que permitirán a los barcos no tripulados desplazarse en presencia de fenómenos ambientales.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/transferencia2022-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/transferencia2022-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/transferencia2022-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/transferencia2022.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p><a href="https://transferencia.tec.mx/2022/01/14/barcos-autonomos-disenados-contra-viento-y-marea/">Read the full article at Transferencia Tec</a></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="media"/><category term="research"/><category term="ASV"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Transferencia Tec feature on designing more robust controllers for unmanned vessels navigating under environmental disturbances.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Innovan ‘A Profundidad’ en Concurso Internacional de Robótica</title><link href="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2020/robosub-innovan/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Innovan ‘A Profundidad’ en Concurso Internacional de Robótica"/><published>2020-10-13T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-10-13T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2020/robosub-innovan</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://alexglzg.github.io/blog/2020/robosub-innovan/"><![CDATA[<p>El equipo VantTec conformado por estudiantes de campus Monterrey se convirtió en el primer equipo mexicano en participar en RoboSub competencia internacional de robótica además de ganar el tercer lugar general.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/blog/robosub2020_es-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/blog/robosub2020_es-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/blog/robosub2020_es-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/blog/robosub2020_es.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p><a href="https://tec.mx/es/noticias/monterrey/educacion/innovan-profundidad-en-concurso-internacional-de-robotica">Read the full article at Tec de Monterrey</a></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="media"/><category term="VantTec"/><category term="RoboSub"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[VantTec se convirtió en el primer equipo mexicano en participar en RoboSub y ganó el tercer lugar general.]]></summary></entry></feed>